content: One of the best AIs in terms of accuracy, speed, and understanding. But it is EXTRAORDINARILY inconsistent, especially with its guidelines. I guess it's like an actual person, as in it has moods. Sometimes it would be fine doing my prompts and the next day, with a very similar prompt, it would reject it. Overall, a good AI that does its job.

you have to numerous times to fix mistakes in output and then it will fix one mistake and then regenerate but not include the entire output. I have asked on one occasion to have a mistake corrected which it did but made more and then would only provide a short output where it corrected the mistake. it is time consuming to try and pieces of output together of corrected outputs. it is obvious that they designed it to just respond with the least amount of characters. I may cancel my subscription

This app is very disappointing. Claude.ai is my go to LLM. I've been using the web app on Android forever. It's fully featured and awesome. Why would I need a native app with a fraction of the functionality? It should be the opposite. The native app should have all the functionality and then some extra features that make use of it's native capabilities. For anyone interested, to install the web app: open claude.ai using chrome, click install when prompted.

Android App: Sorta useless For the Webapp: The most useful AI tool I've tried to date. This app can actually create working programs first shot. I was able to make a couple of fairly complicated scripts with a few prompts. Was never able to get anything anywhere near this useful from chat gpt plus or gemini advanced and I'm only using the FREE version of Claude. The artifacts feature is amazing and so incredibly useful too. This is by far the best AI too yet.

I just updated Claude on an Android 11 phone and I keep getting this error message on the home screen: "We hit a snag loading your projects. Mind giving it another try? Retry" The thing of it is, I have no projects, and more properly it might say,"No projects found." Additionally, at the bottom of the screen a white banner shows up saying, "An error has occurred. Please try again." None of these messages occurred prior to this most recent update. Please be advised.

The product is impressive, and this app is highly useful. However, there are a few issues that need attention: 1. App Opening Issue: The app doesn't open successfully on the first attempt. It requires a second try to launch properly. 2. Connectivity Problem: Occasionally, when I send a message or query, a white banner appears stating "try after some time" due to poor connection, even when the internet is stable. I hope these issues can be addressed promptly by the development team.

You guys have a really wonderful product. Your model is superior and have been proven for your safety. But I reduce 2 stars because: 1) Too limited messages available per day, with ambiguity as to how many are left right from the start 2) Sometimes it gives a message like "Undergoing maintenance for Claude". Something of that sort. The thing is that I lose my precious message opportunity without getting anything at all in this case. Ensure that one chance is spent only with a valid response.

for 24.09.2024 doesnt have editing functionalities for past messages. Also when it generated multiple files "artifacts" in one response i can only acces the last one. Compared to chatgpt on the mobile its mid experience. But on desktop has great project system and those shortcommings are not present there. Anthropic please update the app. I feel like not letting us edit messages is big miss.

The app is very basic compared to the web version and lacking many features and functionalities like: Regenerating new or cycling through Claude's multiple regenerated responses; Editing and cycling through multiple user prompts; Providing feedback on AI responses; Artifacts feature, Starred chats, and Prompt suggestions. Suggestions: Add all the missing features from the web version; Add voice chat for easier and faster interaction.
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback! We're constantly adding new features to the app. Artifacts are now available, and we'll work to add the rest of your suggestions soon. Thanks!

content: Claude is cool. It doesn't feel entirely special to me, but I don't think i am the audience they intend to use their product, so that's fair. Bought premium and still ran out of credits midway through an 8 hour meeting. Had to scramble to find a different ai and cancelled the Claude subscription. 🤙🏼

I really like it, but it seems to be quite glitchy. Today it kept saying prompt is too long even if I just wrote Hello. The lack of character count limit was a pro of this app. As it can be annoying on other Ai models, since the Ai can read it all in half a second.

As a professional writer with 30 years of experience, I've found Claude's proofreading, suggestions for alternative angles, and improvement ideas to be consistently insightful and helpful. After comparing several AI platforms, Claude stood out for its analytical capabilities and nuanced understanding of language. The paid version offers exceptional value, enhancing my writing process significantly. Very worthwhile.

Easily best AI I've used. While I didn't know about conversation limits at first, my questions were a bit vague so Claude explained everything extremely clear and informative so I really feel I got more than the limit gave me. I tried a few other Ai apps before and after but was disappointed so had another extremely productive brief session again today... It will be easy to set half hour a day now Claude shows me how easy I can learn! Great job Anthopic! 👍

Outstanding. I wrote several screenplays and the prospect of turning them into novels was pretty scary. Claude makes the process easy and even makes suggestions as to where to take the story. Think of it as a really good co-writer.

Claude itself is very good. The app is frustrating, with a bewilderingly small subset of the browser functionality. You have to go to the browser to do anything with projects. Why? Additionally, given Claude's finite limit on the maximum size of a conversation, you must include some kind of word count or indication if the conversation size, as once you hit the limit, it's locked.

It's overall a very good app and of course a very smart LLM. I would suggest, however, that they do something similar to ChatGPT in that after you use up all your free promts on the main model they switch you to an older and less intelligent model instead of fully blocking you out. This would keep the incentive to get premium while also balancing accessibility, and it's just a much smarter way to do it.

Every time maintanence how can a regular user use this. There are so many things to improve for more feedback you can contact me i can give many more feedbacks to improve it . With due respect the ceo of claude who is phd in physics has done great job he needs explore to build other domain of ai also.

The current display of code snippets in the mobile app makes it difficult to distinguish code from regular text. To improve readability and user experience, please consider: Using syntax highlighting for code blocks Visually separating code snippets from surrounding text Using a monospace font for code Preserving line breaks and indentation in code blocks These changes would make it much easier to read and understand code examples within conversations.
Simply the best AI assistant I've used so far. It consistently produces useable documents and text, saving me huge amounts of time. I am planning to upgrade to a pro plan in due course.
Great service but flawed in execution. You shouldn't lose any data going from paid to free or free to paid. But you do. Lost all projects and exporting data is zed

I use this for a host of activities from research, to meal planning, event planning, and sounding board for art projects. I love the projects feature and I feel like the quality of the output is high with very rare cases of misunderstanding.

Claude AI is a game-changer! I use it daily for various tasks, from quick calculations to in-depth research. Its ability to understand context and provide thoughtful responses is impressive. Claude even helped me write a book, offering valuable insights and improving my writing style. The app's interface is user-friendly, and responses are fast. It's an incredibly powerful tool for boosting productivity and creativity. Use natural language. Talk to Claude like it's human. Claude will be your BFF

My experience with claude.ai varies from elation to desperation. Just when I think I have fine-tuned my Instructions to claude ai mistake occurs and everything is it seems unable to keep up with what I require. Early days and nodought Claude will probably be if not the best, certainly in the top 3 a.i automation platforms but not quite yet IMHO

Claude Ai is excellent especially with coding and logic but the app and website Contains a lot of glitches Making it unusable. For eg:- If I give a prompt it will start giving output and suddenly Stop then I need to give the prompt multiple times to get an Single Output it's so Annoying

Whether it's social, work related, health related, or legal, Claude has been the greatest subject matter expert and executive assistant. Without exception, it has helped me through various projects and tasks. Perplexity is a close second, but not too close. 🙃 Everyone says I should work for one of these companies. But in reality, those individuals need to really get on board the generative AI train.
I like the conversational tone of Claude. I find it's great for finding out information quickly. my only issue is that prompts frequently fail and have to rerun them multiple times

A few days into using this app, it's clear that it's quite basic at this stage. However, it's clean, responsive, and functions without any issues. You can start new chats and continue old ones, but it lacks features available on the web interface, such as editing, retries, and projects. I'm looking forward to seeing these features added to the Android version for a smoother experience.

Extremely intelligent and useful, understands contexts ans nunances in an amazing way. Only big issue is the awful and atrocious message limit and waiting time and low file size limit. With pro plan I can only manage 30 - 40 messages or so before waiting 4 hours. If this is fixed and message and context limit is imporived I would give it 5 stars for sure. It beats chatgpt out of the water!

I am grateful for Claude. I seek guidance in very different aspects of life. I am rarely disappointed in any of the guidance provided. So very thankful for the wonderful work the engineers have done. Thank you!
Amazing for a multitude of tasks, especially coding. The projects feature is a real game changer.
Great product, highly competitive team, and thoughtful minimalist approach to user experience.
This is not as good an AI model as I thought it was, there are other AI models in the market that provide better services and better features than this and I prefer them over this one.
I loved it as it can visualise and show output of programs. Also useful for diagrams and charts😁
Generally good but unable to provide newer information than April 2024. Chatgpt in the other hand has ability to provide newer information than their latest updated data set in September 2021.
Amazing. Needs more paid plan options and needs voice input/output. Cant fault them fornwither though because they make no claim to do either or promise to in the future

Claude in general is very good, but in my opinion the app is missing a few obvious features: 1. move existing chats into a project, and 2. create and delete projects (I need to use the web interface for this).

Constantly having to retype my prompts due to frequent connectivity errors. This is a design defect. The prompt I typed should not be deleted! Second, another defect prevents me from using dictation to enter a prompt: when I choose the microphone on the SwiftKey keyboard to switch to dictation, the app dismisses the dictation UI and keyboard entirely. Very disappointed as these are critical functions and complete failures of UX design.
This is the 5th Chatbot I have managed to put my hands on amd thus far the most responsive to what my prompts are looking for.I also like the output font and format. Good

The LLM models are great, but the app itself is still not great, bugs happen with a considerably frequency and it has an extremely annoying bug that you write a huge prompt, a bug happens and you lose EVERYTHING you just wrote Extremely annoying, the app code should at least preserve the text so you can try again, and it's not a super difficult technical thing to solve, OpenAI has this solved a long time ago

Claude AI is fantastic and provides the best AI interactions I've experienced. However, it's missing a voice mode, which would be a great addition. I also wish there were options for unlimited conversations with cheaper models after reaching the limit. Overall, it's an awesome app. Update missing edit & regenerate and copy code features..

It's great, but not very ambitious in its current state. It provides a nice clean interface with Claude, but it doesn't provide functionality like artefacts or a voice mode. To me, 5 stars would require supporting those kinds of features and ideally integrating with other applications on the phone. An example might be (securely) giving Claude the ability to ask for your location and then letting it suggest things to do nearby that would be fun.

The user interface could improve. Rather than being greeted in the history section, the app should just start off with a new chat session. The chat should be the main interface wheras the history section should be tucked away in a menu option through button on the top left.

I dont really know how others compare claude to chatgpt, i mean it is ok, but nothing outstanding. but the biggest problem is the app interface, it is ugly and it does not even print code blocks separately, just everything as a single block of text. Also I could not find a way to upgrade my account within the app, even claude claims that it cannot help, this probably is to avoid paying 30% to google.

I literally have to berate Claude to get it to write some stories. If the Prose wasnt so good I'd just drop it and go back to ChatGPT. Anthropic really needs to ease up with the filter. Particularly with writing violent, dark, vengeful stories set in grim settings. Since, well. The darkness in the tone and setting is the point. Also copyright filter is WAY too sensitive.

The AI is outstanding, although I sometimes miss ChatGPT's ability to use tools (but then I just use ChatGPT instead 😄). The app in itself is good. It doesn't really provide anything more than the web interface, as far as I've noticed. I wish people would just make progressive web apps instead of native apps though!

Claude is my go-to LLM for a wide variety of tasks: creative writing inspiration (great for birthday cards), business emails, or processing my Speech-to-Text transcriptions governed by custom instructions. Claude has a variety of speaking tones from very formal and factual to more conversational - though it does feel "put on" and cheesy. I do wish Projects were accessible from the app. To use the Project's feature (which is amazing for continuity amongst a body of work), I still use a browser.

Nice app but it's a ripoff somehow ! Although i subscribed to the get their premium features, still the number of images Are limited with every question you ask. Moreover, there's a "Halt" time where you can't use Claude to ask more questions or to use it's service! I don't understand why do you charge money with such strange way of business. Also the support services is aweful, they didn't answer my inquiries since 10 days now.

Claude AI is a game-changer! This versatile app handles everything from answering questions to assisting with writing and coding. Its natural conversation flow and regular updates keep it cutting-edge. Privacy-focused design is a big plus. While occasional quirks occur, they're minor compared to the immense value it provides. It's like having a brilliant collaborator in your pocket. Highly recommended for anyone seeking a powerful, user-friendly AI assistant!

Looking forward to seeing this developed. It might be a small upgrade from simply using the browser version. Slightly cleaner UI than mobile browser. I can upload context files more smoothly than browser, but can't access starred conversations or projects. Would love to see a speech to text feature so I don't have to keep using chatGPT.

Good but can't copy prompts to clipboard or download threads as doc. Limits the benefit of app vs web in easy retrieval/archival on phone. This rating is for the app, I'll bump up the rating over time as features pour in. The engine is 5 star and performs better than its peers in many scenarios.

It's better than ChatGPT in some ways, but ChatGPT wins hands down with a 10/10 because it doesn't limit you to a maximum of 5 chats every 6 hours. Plus, you can use it for long periods with a lower GPT version. I need to study, and this app isn't reliable due to the chat limit, even though its answers are often better than ChatGPT's.

Reviewing shortly after this launched, it's a pretty bare-bones app so far, but it's clean and responsive, and I haven't had any issues with it. You can start new chats and continue old ones, but it lacks certain features of the web interface, like editing and retries (projects can be used now).

keep hitting the question limit and then they want 20 bucks for Pro? the answer is I get on the free version are hardly ever correct and you have to double check everything to be sure. you think that's worth $20? when this thing is 95% accurate I will pay $20. Right now it seems like it's about 45% accurate. I would pay five bucks and that's about it.

Good app, but please make it so that it doesn't just delete a message when there's an error like an internet connection one It's extremely frustrating for me when I type a long prompt and then when I try to send it and get an error, the message I typed is gone

This is what I have been waiting for! I just need you guys to provide these features in the next to uodates that could potentially give you a 1. Like chatGPT provide some voice assistants with different voices where we can have some voice based conversation with Claude 2. Provide some personalization features like some new fonts and themes. 3. Provide real time information like integrated with browser's

I was waiting for Claude app to be released. And now it's finally here! But I'd like to point this out that the "messages limit" on free tier is very disappointing! Be it free or premium version, there shouldn't be any limitations on messages. And they definitely should do something about their chat ui. The overall ui is pretty boring.

I am just trying it so this is an early rating/view. It looks like it is no different from the web page. The web page maybe just producing a web app. And it seems to require the phone number now. Is that correct? it's unusual that it needs an email address and also a phone number... It is worse. it's simply does not even allow me to sign up. I do get the verification code for the email however it says an error occurred when I try to get the verification code for My phone number...

The best in class LLM on the market. It's ability to abstract and project trends based on documentation is second to none. While it's math is not 100% yet, its probably the closest, and Sonnet's breakdown of its calculations allows for easy fixes when necessary.

What's the point of making an app when your most innovative section 'projects' is not available in app. Only thing I can see is the previous chats, but if I want to access a chat in a specific project, I can't do that (may be I have missed that but can't see the projects). Add the project section as well, otherwise for paid users like me, there is no use of app.

Claude is a powerful and versatile generative AI chatbot. The only reason I give four stars is because I regularly get a message that the internet is not connected when it is and I have to restart the app in order to discover that the prompt was answered.
It has the artifact and project capabilities of the website, a familiar interface, and just simply works, seamlessly

Implement these useful features, implement CodeBlock UI like web application theme. it's makes code more readable and colorful. And add edit prompts feature like web application and add chat management features like clear, export, delete chat history with single click, Implement these features in upcoming updates on mobile platforms. Then I will give five ⭐ to this ✨ application.

No voice chat, no internet search, severe limits and caps (paid account) on numbers & sizes of messages which expire everyday for coders. And just to recall, you hadn't even released the android app for until much later after iOS release! It is unfortunate that while your model and core capabilities are so outstanding, the product ecosystem and prioritising users' experience has been abysmal. Stop making us pay for ChatGPT and yourself - both, every month and switch between both every day!
It's a great tool for use , but one issue is that after using it for sometime, it keeps on saying the prompt is too long while the prompt is only two lines.

Sonnet 3.5 beats the GPT-o model, in my honest opinion—and I've used them both to write everything from emails to book series. Claude (Sonnet 3.5) better follows instructions, more creatively expresses English prose (while conforming better to tonal/stylistic prompt and following instructions more oftenl. CAVEAT: YOUR MILEAGE MAY VARY. CLAUDE GUARDRAILS ARE BEST IN CLASS. AI REFUSES ANSWERS & TOPICS IT DEEMS ANTITHETICAL TO ITS ETHICAL PROGRAMMING.

The capability of Claude, is insane. Unfortunately I am facing a bit of a problem, I am being forced to login every time I open the app. Please fix this guys. I don't want to use chat gpt or gemini, but if this continues...

Excellent LLM out there. best in the market right now. unmatched outputs saving ample of time for our team. I have a pro subscription and it works well. ChatGPT 4O is nothing compared to this. I like the creativity it brings to table.

Very impressive. More detailed especially in attributing sources. Also really helpful in building prompts. By intelligently asking for more information I actually got to the right results more quickly. Sometimes a little hit and miss on general research but I can use other AI for that
Loses prompts. Sometimes you'll get an internal sever error. It happens. No big deal but if i just spent a bunch of time typing out a reply at least keep it until it's actually sent.

I am thoroughly impressed by the exceptional service it offers. The platform is incredibly intuitive, with responses that are both accurate and contextually relevant. The ease of use and the quality of interactions make it stand out among similar services. Whether for personal or professional use, Claude AI delivers reliable and insightful support every time. I highly recommend Claude AI to anyone in need of a powerful and user-friendly AI. P.S. Review written with the help of ChatGpt by OpenAi

Tried using claude for coding. Turns out it is worthless and all the promotions that they are doing is just fake. Encountered frequent drops of service on this AI. This is worthless. ChatGPT is a 1000% better than this. Please stay away from this. Turn this company into ash. This is worthless and deserves to be in a dump. Waste of time.
Excellent. Good phrasing; can (rarely though) get confused if the problem isn't chunked.
there is Many problems with this AI. like many times I submit a prompt. it shows to larger prompt. "Day8 completed" is this is a big prompt?
Absolutely AMAZING 👏 😍 ❤ 👌 I think I'm in love. This program is so intuitive and it's responses are on point. Highly recommend it!!!
Superb my learning become 10 times faster. I am btech student in bits Pilani. But you should give a proper prompt
this Ai is amazing but should increase the number of replies and also add a feature that accepts longer prompts overall great app highly recommended
Very good conversational AI. Feel more human the other ones I tried. Wish the pro version were a bit cheaper though, I just can't afford the subscription otherwise I would have subscribed.
Excellent GenAI app with quality responses, serving as a personal assistant and mentor to fuel my productivity. Please bring the READ ALOUD feature.

Claude Sonnet 3.5 is seriously overrated in performance, and overpriced in comparison to ChatGPT4o. Its response to complicated queries are not accurate, and frequently hallucinates. It also has the annoying limitation of how many questions you can ask in a given period of time, which is totally unfair. Your pro-monthly subscription is the same price as ChatGPT4o, then how come GPT4o has no limitation and its responses are much better?? Not worth the money if you use AI for complex tasks.

I am using claude for programming and without any doubt there is no comparison of Claude, not even chatgpt 4o can solve the complex tasks that claude solves for me. Although i would like if claude makes the free version with more prompts as it's very much limited.

I'm using Claude 3.5 Pro which is a great LLM, however this app doesn't seem to show starred chats nor allow searching previous chats. The website interface for Claude does allow these things, so this app seems incomplete for now.

Paid subscriber. It's getting better but I hope it can integrate with the internet like chaggpt does with searching the world but in Claude way without compromising privacy. Also I hope it could talk back to back like a natural person.

Claude is a game-changer for organizing daily tasks and boosting productivity. Its sleek, user-friendly interface makes planning and tracking goals effortless, with reliable performance and thoughtful design, Claude stands out as an essential tool for staying organized and on top of your game.
My personal favorite 😍 AI. Works flawlessly and takes feedback well. Thank you for this incredible as d amazing tool it helps me in both my personal and professional life.
well integrated (they just added projects, too!) and the models themselves are exceptional. Their approach to ui design and user accessibility is also very cool.

Too limited in its messaging. Why are you limiting messages? Chat GPT literally allows unlimited messaging on free version, plus I can add documents for it to analyze. But here, you have to pay, and barely get to talk, which is too cumbersome.
limited access from the beginning is so disappointing, I don't feel to buy the premium.

claude is the best llm app out there love the ui and it's coding abilities. just there one problem that they have message cap - so you probably can't have deep conversations like you use to have with chatgpt. but still the best I love anthropic and hope they win this ai race.

Currently the best chatbot model with 3.5 Sonnet. Good app. No voice input yet like GPT, but well worth it for the superior intelligence right now. Good company that doesn't tease features and products.
One of the best LLM at the moment that provides free access to its algorithms, very pleasant and understandable in communication, often used in working with documents and projects
I can work with my projects on the go, without subjecting myself to mobile browser hell. Rating goes up; I'm a simple man.
Looking forward to the progression and advancement of AI. Love the app!!
it's a fantastic tool, it has pretty nifty features, plus it's powerful generative AI
fast and thoughtful answers, especially programming languages related.

I love this app especially how it is always willing to expand on any answer it provides.

still limited and generic. biased against prompting in further questions

Yes! Just Yes! Absolutely fantastic! Been comparing open AI (pro), Gemini (pro) Meta ai, code seeker, etc with Claude (pro) and find myself basically using both chatGPT 4o and Claude 3.5 all the time. Sometimes Claude wins, sometimes 4o, both mind blowing

Claude is amazing. I have been sleeping on it for so long but better late than never. It's very coherent and interprets Prompts effectively. Appears the model has substantial RHLF ongoing. Well done to the team

Okay, it's amazing. It's much more intelligent than ChatGPT and it helps me to solve a lot of my daily problems. If you know how to write a good prompt and if you know how to take help of it then honestly you'd be using this daily.

Best so far if compared to similar apps in the AI field. It would be great that there were no daily limits or that premium got cheaper. But so far so good, thanks!

The most erudite and well informed LLM that I have had the pleasure of interacting with. There also appears to be less hallucination than was evident in competing products. Anthropic has given us something special here!

I have thoroughly tested various GPT models, including the most well-known ones. Unfortunately, the results I obtained did not meet my expectations. Finally, I asked same question to claude, the answer and step by step solving process was really amazin

Why even post this app? If we are paying premium services and can't even use them from the app? The projects are missing and that is the only thing I care for since claude memory is about as good as my dementia grandmother .

Claude AI - AI Assistant ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ 5.0 It is a Powerful AI assistant for writing, analysis, coding and more. Fast responses, wide knowledge, and helpful across many tasks. Overall: Highly capable AI assistant, great for productivity and learning
Works absolutely perfect. No problems that I can point out so far. Would be nice if Claude had voice though, but so far so good
It's great but why there is no way to copy the prompts you entered! That's a big issue please fix it. Otherwise, 5 star is to go.
Claude is handsome the best API I've used. the ability to add files to a project is hands down the best thing ever.

Subject: Request for Increased Free Usage Limit for Anthropic Services Dear Anthropic Team, I hope this finds you well. As an avid user, I greatly benefit from your tools and services. Understanding there are premium plans, I propose an increase in the current free usage limits. Thank you.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback! We're adjusting free limits as fast as we can keep up with. Claude Pro comes with 5x more usage and access to our other models and will be the best way to use Claude more if you are running out of free chats. Please let us know if there is anything else we could do better too. Thanks!

content: More extensive training in programming and offensive cybersecurity is definitely needed. Still, great app!

The waiting time is too long for a pro user.. just used 30 minutes after that it says wait for 4 hours, I don't get it! how am I the pro user then? I want to pay you more but I need my solution right now, don't wanna wait.. please fix the issue ASAP!
Very robust chatbot. The app now has feature parity with web version. With projects and artifacts.
Outstanding app. The problem is that free users have only limited access. Anthropic should do something or openAi will the competition.
Good app. doesn't have as many features as GPT 4, but Claude is more sympathetic and provides great benefits.

Not sure how it's possible to make a user interface this atrocious, there is no code copy button, no proper way to view files and artifacts, the app just looks ugly and the code isn't centered properly in a code block. It looks horribly rushed. To be honest, the cheap darkened cream yellow "banana milkshake" colour is ugly, and anthropic needs to ditch it. It gives the user a queasy feeling, unlike OpenAI's clean, slick white design for their app. There is no proper way to search for chats.

short windows, limited questions, shallow generalized responses, very counter productive, they actively works against me, fails to meet word count every time, reductionism is rapant and destroys your work. no customer service, very unsatisfied, very disappointed in them selling out to Amazon. if there was less than one stars I would give it. pretty good so far. The model gets stuck after a long conversation in this version, says prompt too long
it's awesome 💯 but sometimes even in pro plan I am hit with messages limit and long prompts are still slow

Often incorrect and over sensitive. AI is like carrying an overprotective wine mom in your pocket... They are so annoying and so wrong so often.

I can't see Project management, but otherwise fine for on the couch.

This is amazing. As a volunteer for a children's art program and a remote spay clinic in Mexico, this App.has been invaluable for our nonprofits It is a monumental time saver.

content: Claude is cool. It doesn't feel entirely special to me, but I don't think i am the audience they intend to use their product, so that's fair. I really like it, but it seems to be quite glitchy. Today it kept saying prompt is too long even if I just wrote Hello. The lack of character count limit was a pro of this app. As it can be annoying on other Ai models, since the Ai can read it all in half a second.

As a professional writer with 30 years of experience, I've found Claude's proofreading, suggestions for alternative angles, and improvement ideas to be consistently insightful and helpful. After comparing several AI platforms, Claude stood out for its analytical capabilities and nuanced understanding of language. The paid version offers exceptional value, enhancing my writing process significantly. Very worthwhile.

Easily best AI I've used. While I didn't know about conversation limits at first, my questions were a bit vague so Claude explained everything extremely clear and informative so I really feel I got more than the limit gave me. I tried a few other Ai apps before and after but was disappointed so had another extremely productive brief session again today... It will be easy to set half hour a day now Claude shows me how easy I can learn! Great job Anthopic! 👍

Outstanding. I wrote several screenplays and the prospect of turning them into novels was pretty scary. Claude makes the process easy and even makes suggestions as to where to take the story. Think of it as a really good co-writer.

Claude itself is very good. The app is frustrating, with a bewilderingly small subset of the browser functionality. You have to go to the browser to do anything with projects. Why? Additionally, given Claude's finite limit on the maximum size of a conversation, you must include some kind of word count or indication if the conversation size, as once you hit the limit, it's locked.

It's overall a very good app and of course a very smart LLM. I would suggest, however, that they do something similar to ChatGPT in that after you use up all your free promts on the main model they switch you to an older and less intelligent model instead of fully blocking you out. This would keep the incentive to get premium while also balancing accessibility, and it's just a much smarter way to do it.

This app is very disappointing. Claude.ai is my go to LLM. I've been using the web app on Android forever. It's fully featured and awesome. Why would I need a native app with a fraction of the functionality? It should be the opposite. The native app should have all the functionality and then some extra features that make use of it's native capabilities. For anyone interested, to install the web app: open claude.ai using chrome, click install when prompted.

Every time maintanence how can a regular user use this. There are so many things to improve for more feedback you can contact me i can give many more feedbacks to improve it . Android App: Sorta useless For the Webapp: The most useful AI tool I've tried to date. This app can actually create working programs first shot. I was able to make a couple of fairly complicated scripts with a few prompts. Was never able to get anything anywhere near this useful from chat gpt plus or gemini advanced and I'm only using the FREE version of Claude. The artifacts feature is amazing and so incredibly useful too. This is by far the best AI too yet.

The current display of code snippets in the mobile app makes it difficult to distinguish code from regular text. To improve readability and user experience, please consider: Using syntax highlighting for code blocks Visually separating code snippets from surrounding text Using a monospace font for code Preserving line breaks and indentation in code blocks These changes would make it much easier to read and understand code examples within conversations.

The user interface could improve. Rather than being greeted in the history section, the app should just start off with a new chat session. The chat should be the main interface wheras the history section should be tucked away in a menu option through button on the top left.

replyContent: Thank you for the feedback! We're adjusting free limits as fast as we can keep up with. Claude Pro comes with 5x more usage and access to our other models and will be the best way to use Claude more if you are running out of free chats. content: Claude is cool. It doesn't feel entirely special to me, but I don't think i am the audience they intend to use their product, so that's fair. I really like it, but it seems to be quite glitchy. Today it kept saying prompt is too long even if I just wrote Hello. The lack of character count limit was a pro of this app. As it can be annoying on other Ai models, since the Ai can read it all in half a second.

As a professional writer with 30 years of experience, I've found Claude's proofreading, suggestions for alternative angles, and improvement ideas to be consistently insightful and helpful. After comparing several AI platforms, Claude stood out for its analytical capabilities and nuanced understanding of language. The paid version offers exceptional value, enhancing my writing process significantly. Very worthwhile.

Easily best AI I've used. While I didn't know about conversation limits at first, my questions were a bit vague so Claude explained everything extremely clear and informative so I really feel I got more than the limit gave me. I tried a few other Ai apps before and after but was disappointed so had another extremely productive brief session again today... It will be easy to set half hour a day now Claude shows me how easy I can learn! Great job Anthopic! 👍

Outstanding. I wrote several screenplays and the prospect of turning them into novels was pretty scary. Claude makes the process easy and even makes suggestions as to where to take the story. Think of it as a really good co-writer.

Claude itself is very good. The app is frustrating, with a bewilderingly small subset of the browser functionality. You have to go to the browser to do anything with projects. Why? Additionally, given Claude's finite limit on the maximum size of a conversation, you must include some kind of word count or indication if the conversation size, as once you hit the limit, it's locked.

It's overall a very good app and of course a very smart LLM. I would suggest, however, that they do something similar to ChatGPT in that after you use up all your free promts on the main model they switch you to an older and less intelligent model instead of fully blocking you out. This would keep the incentive to get premium while also balancing accessibility, and it's just a much smarter way to do it.

This app is very disappointing. Claude.ai is my go to LLM. I've been using the web app on Android forever. It's fully featured and awesome. Why would I need a native app with a fraction of the functionality? It should be the opposite. The native app should have all the functionality and then some extra features that make use of it's native capabilities. For anyone interested, to install the web app: open claude.ai using chrome, click install when prompted.

Every time maintanence how can a regular user use this. There are so many things to improve for more feedback you can contact me i can give many more feedbacks to improve it . Android App: Sorta useless For the Webapp: The most useful AI tool I've tried to date. This app can actually create working programs first shot. Was never able to get anything anywhere near this useful from chat gpt plus or gemini advanced and I'm only using the FREE version of Claude. The artifacts feature is amazing and so incredibly useful too. This is by far the best AI too yet.

The current display of code snippets in the mobile app makes it difficult to distinguish code from regular text. To improve readability and user experience, please consider: Using syntax highlighting for code blocks Visually separating code snippets from surrounding text Using a monospace font for code Preserving line breaks and indentation in code blocks These changes would make it much easier to read and understand code examples within conversations.
Simply the best AI assistant I've used so far. It consistently produces useable documents and text, saving me huge amounts of time. I am planning to upgrade to a pro plan in due course.

Second, another defect prevents me from using dictation to enter a prompt: when I choose the microphone on the SwiftKey keyboard to switch to dictation, the app dismisses the dictation UI and keyboard entirely. Very disappointed as these are critical functions and complete failures of UX design.

To me, 5 stars would require supporting those kinds of features and ideally integrating with other applications on the phone. An example might be (securely) giving Claude the ability to ask for your location and then letting it suggest things to do nearby that would be fun.

The user interface could improve. Rather than being greeted in the history section, the app should just start off with a new chat session. The chat should be the main interface wheras the history section should be tucked away in a menu option through button on the top left.

Claude has a variety of speaking tones from very formal and factual to more conversational - though it does feel "put on" and cheesy. I do wish Projects were accessible from the app. To use the Project's feature (which is amazing for continuity amongst a body of work), I still use a browser.

Nice app but it's a ripoff somehow ! Although i subscribed to the get their premium features, still the number of images Are limited with every question you ask. Claude AI is a game-changer! This versatile app handles everything from answering questions to assisting with writing and coding. Its natural conversation flow and regular updates keep it cutting-edge. Privacy-focused design is a big plus. While occasional quirks occur, they're minor compared to the immense value it provides. It's like having a brilliant collaborator in your pocket. Highly recommended for anyone seeking a powerful, user-friendly AI assistant!

Plus, you can use it for long periods with a lower GPT version. I need to study, and this app isn't reliable due to the chat limit, even though its answers are often better than ChatGPT's.
